# Python conventions (this repo)

## Imports and structure

- Prefer existing patterns: `graph.config.get_config`, `graph.utils.logger.logger`, `call_llm_api.LLMCompletionCall`.
- Keep changes localized; match surrounding style (types, docstrings).

## LLM outputs

- Parse model output with **`json_repair.loads`** when JSON may be malformed.
- **Entity resolution** (`utils/resolution.py`): model must return `{"same": [ ... ]}`—one boolean per candidate pair, same order as the prompt. Strip optional ` ```json ` fences before parse. Do not reintroduce line-based `pair N: yes` without updating both prompt and parser.

## Graph / API

- Graph data is collection-scoped under `./data/graph/{collection_id}.json`; preserve this path contract when editing callers.
- Pydantic response models document API fields; keep field names stable for clients.

## Running

- Use **uv** to run the app, e.g. `uv run uvicorn graph_server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 20050` (adjust if project adds scripts in `pyproject.toml`).
